southerly buster
Homonym Number:
Word Class:noun
Sense Number: 1
Definition:a cold wind from the south, usually bringing stormy rain, sleet and snow.
Origin:[none]
Register:
Register 2:
Flag: Farm Words
Domain:Rural
Region:[none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: also southerly burster, rarely southern burster
